# Topic Modeling with SVD and NMF

### Singular Value Decomposition

SVD is Matrix Factorization technique used in Topic Modeling for reducing the dimensions of the matrix which represents (Document & Terms). The idea behind SVD is finding words which occur frequently in one topic and does not occur another topic which will give us document specific important words revealing the topic.

The matrix is Document in rows and the vocabulary as columns and occurence value as interseption.

SVD is an exact decomposition meaning that multipling back the matrices again will return the original matrix.

