### Non-Negative Matrix Factorization

>"Nonnegative matrix factorization (NMF) has become a widely used tool for the analysis of high dimensional data as it automatically extracts sparse and meaningful features from a set of nonnegative data vectors."

NMF approximates a matrix X with low-rank matrix approximation such that X approx. W *H. Where the properties does not have values below 0 which makes it Non-Negative

Also NMF is a non-exact decomposition where if you want to generate original matrix there is an reconstruction error.

